docs.lead_paragraph: It is interesting, with each recurring Autumn, to watch the city fill up again with its returned residents. The clientele of the New-York shops in July and August is as different from that which throngs their doors through the rest of the year as the strollers on Murray Hill in the dog days are unlike the usual frequenters of that aristocratic neighborhood.
